  "sku": "US0055-2019",
  "short_description": "<ul>\n<li><strong>Type</strong>: Red Wine</li>\n<li><strong>Country</strong>: USA</li>\n<li><strong>Region</strong>: Napa Valley</li>\n<li><strong>Varietals</strong>: Cabernet Sauvignon, Petit Verdot</li>\n<li><strong>Vintage</strong>: 2019</li>\n<li><strong>Alcohol</strong>: 15%</li>\n<li><strong>Volume</strong>: 750ml</li>\n<li><strong>Vivino Rating</strong>: 4.6</li>\n<li><strong>Style</strong>: Full-Bodied, Natural</li>\n<li><strong>Pairing</strong>: Best served with all types of classic meat dishes, game, burgers, barbecue, grilled dishes and stews. READINESS FOR DRINKING Aged for 22 months in new French oak.</li>\n</ul>",
  "description": "<h3>Key characteristics:</h3>\n<p><strong>Chappellet Pritchard Hill Cabernet Sauvignon 2019</strong> is a red wine from Napa Valley, USA, made from 90% Cabernet Sauvignon, 10% Petit Verdot.</p>\n<h3>Tasting Notes:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Variety</strong>: 90% Cabernet Sauvignon, 10% Petit Verdot.</li>\n<li><strong>Appearance</strong>: Elegant and classy deep ruby..</li>\n<li><strong>Aroma</strong>: This wine displays depth and complexity. Pure, intense aromas of blackberry, cassis, perfumed violets, graphite and macerated berry skins leap from the glass, followed by layers of anise, vanilla, clove and chocolate..</li>\n<li><strong>Taste</strong>: The luxurious dark berry and spice notes continue on the.</li>\n<li><strong>Pairing</strong>: Best served with all types of classic meat dishes, game, burgers, barbecue, grilled dishes and stews. READINESS FOR DRINKING Aged for 22 months in new French oak..</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Overall impression:</h3>\n<p>Chappellet Pritchard Hill Cabernet Sauvignon is a food-friendly selection from Vinum Lector, added to the SpiritHouse catalogue from the current supplier portfolio.</p>\n<h3>Extra notes:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Source: Vinum Lector product page.</li>\n</ul>",
