  "permalink": "https://spirithouse.com/tohu-marewa-single-vineyard-sauvignon-blanc/",
  "sku": "NZ0083",
  "short_description": "<ul>\n<li><strong>Type</strong>: White Wine</li>\n<li><strong>Country</strong>: New Zealand</li>\n<li><strong>Region</strong>: Marlborough</li>\n<li><strong>Varietals</strong>: Sauvignon Blanc</li>\n<li><strong>Vintage</strong>: 2024</li>\n<li><strong>Alcohol</strong>: 12.5%</li>\n<li><strong>Volume</strong>: 750ml</li>\n<li><strong>Vivino Rating</strong>: 4.1</li>\n<li><strong>Style</strong>: Fresh, Natural, Sustainable</li>\n<li><strong>Pairing</strong>: Its textured, creamy mouthfeel makes it highly food-friendly. It pairs excellently with versatile seafood dishes, creamy soft cheeses, or poultry. Additional information</li>\n</ul>",
  "description": "<h3>Key characteristics:</h3>\n<p><strong>Tohu Marewa Single Vineyard Sauvignon Blanc 2024</strong> is a white wine from Marlborough, New Zealand, made from Sauvignon Blanc.</p>\n<h3>Tasting Notes:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Variety</strong>: Sauvignon Blanc.</li>\n<li><strong>Appearance</strong>: Pale straw/gold with brilliant green shades..</li>\n<li><strong>Aroma</strong>: It exhibits a refined bouquet with subtle layers of nettle, red capsicum and tropical pineapple aromas..</li>\n<li><strong>Taste</strong>: Concentrated and textural with stonefruit, zesty citrus, blackcurrant leaf, supported by subtle French oak. Bright, pure and long finish with refined minerality. A vibrant yet layered Single Vineyard Sauvignon Blanc with lifted aromatics and understated oak complexity. AGEING 30% percent of the blend undergoes a ‘wild’ ferment in 500 litre French oak puncheons, with the remaining 70% fermented at low temperatures in stainless steel..</li>\n<li><strong>Pairing</strong>: Its textured, creamy mouthfeel makes it highly food-friendly. It pairs excellently with versatile seafood dishes, creamy soft cheeses, or poultry. Additional information.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Overall impression:</h3>\n<p>Tohu Marewa Single Vineyard Sauvignon Blanc is a food-friendly selection from Vinum Lector, added to the SpiritHouse catalogue from the current supplier portfolio.</p>\n<h3>Extra notes:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Source: Vinum Lector product page.</li>\n</ul>",
